Jenkins Agents
agent any - run on any available agent/nodes
agent none - no global agent
agent { label 'linux' } / agent { node { label 'docker' } } - runs on a jenkins node that has been tagged with the label docker
docker should be installed & Docker Pipeline plugin should be enabled
agent { docker { image 'maven:3.8.1' } } - runs inside docker container. need to install docker pipeline pl
agent { dockerfile true } - build and run inside a Docker container defined by a Dockerfile in your repo

to add the new vm as agent in jenkins
install java n jenkins user on that VM. install whatever tools that may be required for build jobs
In jenkins manage jenkins -> nodes -> add node - node name, label and other options, launch method - ssh / controller

Jenkins Triggers
Poll SCM - triggers for source code changes. only works based on schedule. no new commit triggers immediately
Build Periodically - cron schedule
SCM Webhooks (Push Events) - install source plugins(git / gitlab / bitbucket). configure source as git from UI in freestyle project & from code in pipeline project(can choose when to trigger push/pull request). create webhook in git provider and provider url as jenkins job url or jenkins git provider plugin url
or manage jenkins -> systems -> add gitlab creds here also to be accessed by all the jobs globally
Build after other projects are built

environments {} - can be used in the pipeline level or stage level for variables

withCredentials([string(credentialsId: 'sonarqube', variable: 'SONAR_AUTH_TOKEN')]) - scoped to step. ex. sonarqube is the temp variable name, SONAR_AUTH_TOKEN is the actual jenkins cred name
environment { REGISTRY_CREDENTIALS = credentials('docker-cred')} - scoped to entire pipeline or stage based on where its defined. 
withCredentials output types - string, username/password(USR & PWD), file

